1.	Dataset Difficulty Ranking (Conceptual Calibration) 数据集难度排名（概念校准）

In this lab, you will compare five datasets discussed in the lecture: MNIST, CIFAR-10, Flowers-17, Kaggle Dogs vs Cats, and ImageNet. Your task is to rank them from easiest to hardest, where 1 represents the easiest classification problem最简单的分类问题 and 5 the most difficult.
Your ranking must be justified in writing. In your explanation, you should consider factors such as image resolution, number of classes, intra-class variation, dataset size, background complexity, and overall real-world variability. Explain clearly why one dataset is more challenging than another rather than relying on intuition or reputation.

A1.1: Dataset Difficulty Ranking (Conceptual Calibration)

Step 1 – Understand the Five Datasets
The key characteristics of each dataset:
# Dataset	         # Classes类别	  # Image Size	   # Images (approx)	   # Key Challenges
MNIST	               10	          28×28 grey	    70,000	                Simple shapes, centred, clean background
CIFAR-10	           10	          32×32 RGB      	60,000	                Real objects, cluttered backgrounds, intra class variation 真实物体，杂乱背景，类内差异
Flowers-17	           17	          variable	        1,360 (80/class)	    Small data, fine grained, scale/pose variation  小规模数据，精细粒度，尺度/姿态变化
Kaggle Dogs vs Cats	   2	          variable	        25,000.                 Real world photos, background clutter, varied poses 真实世界照片，背景杂乱，姿态多样
ImageNet	           1000           variable	        1.4M 22000 categories	Massive scale, fine grained, extreme variability 大规模数据，精细粒度，极端差异

Step 2 – Define Difficulty Factors 定义难度因素
•	Image resolution 图像分辨率 – higher resolution can mean more detail, but also more noise. 更高的分辨率意味着更多的细节，但也意味着更多的噪声。
•	Number of classes 类别数量 – more classes generally increase difficulty. 类别越多，难度通常越大。
•	Intra class variation 类内差异 –  objects of the same class look very different (e.g., dogs in different poses, backgrounds).同一类别的物体看起来可能截然不同（例如，不同姿态、不同背景的狗）。
•	Dataset size 数据集大小 – smaller datasets are harder to generalise from. 数据集大小 – 较小的数据集更难进行泛化
•	Background complexity 背景复杂性 – cluttered backgrounds make object recognition harder. 杂乱的背景会增加物体识别的难度。
•	Real world variability 真实世界的变异性- includes lighting, occlusion, viewpoint changes.包括光照、遮挡、视角变化

Step 3 – Rank from Easiest to Hardest (1 = easiest, 5 = hardest)
Based on the above factors, a reasonable ranking is:
1.	MNIST – extremely constrained, clean, low variation, large enough for its simplicity.
2.	Kaggle Dogs vs Cats – only two classes, large dataset, but real world variability makes it harder than MNIST.
3.	CIFAR 10 – more classes (10), small images, but significant intra class variation and background clutter. 但存在显著的类内差异和背景杂乱。
4.	Flowers 17 – small dataset, fine grained distinctions, high variation in scale/background, though only 17 classes.
5.	ImageNet – 1000 classes, huge intra class variation, real world complexity, massive scale.

Step 4 – Justify the Ranking in Writing
MNIST is the easiest because digits are centred, have consistent size, and the background is plain black. In contrast, ImageNet is the hardest: it contains 1000 diverse categories with objects photographed under every conceivable condition, requiring models to learn truly generalisable features. MNIST 数据集最简单，因为数字居中、大小一致，且背景为纯黑色。相比之下，ImageNet 数据集最难：它包含 1000 个不同的类别，物体在各种可能条件下拍摄，这要求模型学习真正具有泛化能力的特征。

