A1.3: Reflect on “Dataset Difficulty”
Dataset difficulty is a multi faceted concept多方面的概念. It is not simply the number of classes, but the interplay互相作用 of class count, intra class variation, image quality, dataset size, and real world noise. A dataset with few classes but high variation can be far more challenging than one with many classes but highly controlled settings. 数据集难度是一个多方面的概念。它不仅仅指类别数量，而是类别数量、类内变异、图像质量、数据集大小以及真实世界噪声等因素相互作用的结果。一个类别少但变异大的数据集可能比一个类别多但设置高度可控的数据集更具挑战性。







2.	The Illusion of Accuracy准确性的错觉

Imagine that one student trains a neural network on MNIST and achieves 99 percent accuracy. Another student trains a model on Flowers-17 and achieves 72 percent accuracy. At first glance, the first model appears superior第一个模型似乎更胜一筹. However, this comparison比较 is incomplete 并不全面and potentially misleading具有误导性.
In this section, you must analyze why accuracy alone is insufficient for evaluating model quality分析为什么仅凭准确率不足以评估模型的质量. Discuss how dataset complexity数据集的复杂性, number of classes类别的数量, and variation变异性 influence achievable accuracy可达到的准确性. Consider whether 72 percent on a small, highly variable dataset might represent stronger modeling ability than near-perfect performance on a simple dataset.

A2.1: 
Step 1 – Recognise Why Accuracy Alone is Misleading
Explain that accuracy must be interpreted in the context of the dataset. 99% on MNIST is expected, while 72% on Flowers‑17 may indicate a very strong model because the dataset is small and highly variable. The absolute number tells me nothing without knowing the baseline or the difficulty. 解释一下，准确率必须结合数据集来解读。在 MNIST 数据集上达到 99% 的准确率是预期的，而在 Flowers-17 数据集上达到 72% 的准确率可能表明模型非常出色，因为该数据集规模较小且变异性很高。如果不了解基线数据或难度，绝对值本身并不能说明任何问题。

Step 2 – Analyse the Flowers 17 vs MNIST Example
Achieving 72% on Flowers 17 likely requires the model to handle fine grained differences, varied backgrounds, and limited training examples – a much harder task than recognising centred digits. Thus the lower accuracy may actually reflect superior modelling ability.

Extend your reasoning further. Suppose a model achieves 95 percent accuracy on CIFAR-10. What hidden problems could still exist? Could there be dataset leakages数据集泄露 between training and test sets? Could the model be overfitting过度拟合 subtle background patterns rather than learning object structure? Could the test set be too similar to the training set?

A2.2: Extend to CIFAR 10 (95% accuracy)
Consider hidden problems even with high accuracy:
•	Data leakage数据泄露 – if test images accidentally resemble training images (e.g., same source), the score is inflated分数会被虚高.
•	Overfitting to backgrounds过度拟合背景 – the model might learn that dogs often appear on grass, so it looks for grass rather than the dog.
•	Test set similarity测试集相似性 – if the test set is too easy (e.g., all images in similar conditions), the score doesn’t reflect real world performance实际性能.

