3.	Dataset Size and Modeling Strategy数据集规模和建模策略

Consider two separate scenarios. In the first scenario, you have access to only 80 labeled images per class, similar in scale to Flowers-17. In the second scenario, you have access to over one million labeled images across one thousand categories, comparable in scale to ImageNet.
For the small-data scenario小规模场景, explain what training strategy you would adopt. Discuss whether you would train a neural network from scratch or rely on transfer learning. Explain the concept of freezing layers and fine-tuning冻结层和微调, and justify your reasoning in terms of overfitting risk and feature reuse过拟合风险和特征重用.

A3.1: Small-data scenario - Strategy: Transfer Learning with Fine Tuning
•	Why not train from scratch? – With so few images, a deep network will massively overfit过度拟合.
•	Transfer learning迁移学习 – Start from a model pre trained on ImageNet (or similar large dataset). Its lower layers have learned generic features (edges边缘, textures纹理) that are reusable.
•	Freezing layers冻结层 – Typically freeze the early convolutional layers卷积层 (so their weights are not updated) and only train the classifier head (the final fully connected layers) on the new data. This prevents overfitting 防止过度拟合and speeds up training. 通常冻结早期的卷积层（使其权重不更新），仅使用新数据训练分类器头部（最后的全连接层）。这可以防止过拟合并加快训练速度。
•	Fine tuning微调 – Optionally, after training the head, we can unfreeze some of the top convolutional layers 卷积层 and continue training with a very low learning rate to adapt the features slightly to the new domain. This must be done carefully to avoid overfitting. 可选地，在训练完头部后，我们可以解冻一些顶部的卷积层，并以非常低的学习率继续训练，以使特征略微适应新的领域。必须谨慎操作以避免过拟合。

For the large-scale scenario, describe how your approach changes. Consider computational requirements, training time, model capacity, and regularization. Discuss how the availability of massive data reduces certain risks while introducing new engineering challenges. 考虑计算需求、训练时间、模型容量和正则化。讨论海量数据的可用性如何在降低某些风险的同时，也带来新的工程挑战。

A3.2: Large-data scenario – Strategy: Train from Scratch (or continue pre training)
•	Why train from scratch? – With massive data, a deep network can learn robust features稳健的特征 without overfitting 不会过度拟合. I have enough data to train all layers.
•	Computational requirements计算需求 – I need powerful hardware (multiple GPUs/TPUs) and distributed training techniques分布式训练技术.
•	Training time – Can be days or weeks; requires careful scheduling and checkpointing检查点机制.
•	Model capacity 模型容量– I can afford larger models 可以构建更大的模型 (e.g., ResNet 50, EfficientNet B7) because the data will not cause overfitting.
•	Regularisation正则化 – Even with large data, regularisation (dropout, weight decay衰减, data augmentation增强) is still useful to improve generalisation模型的泛化能力.
•	Engineering challenges – Managing data pipelines管道, distributed training, and experiment tracking becomes critical. 数据管道管理、分布式训练和实验跟踪变得至关重要

Conclude this section by explaining how dataset size fundamentally shapes modeling decisions. 本节最后解释数据集大小如何从根本上影响建模决策。

A3.3: Dataset size is the primary driver of modeling strategy. Small datasets force the use of transfer learning to avoid overfitting and leverage pre learned features. Large datasets allow training from scratch, enabling the learning of highly specialised features, but introduce computational and engineering challenges. The choice of architecture架构, regularisation正则化, and training procedure训练过程 all hinge on the amount of data available.数据集的大小是建模策略的主要驱动因素。小数据集迫使模型采用迁移学习来避免过拟合，并利用预先学习的特征。大数据集允许从头开始训练，从而学习高度专业化的特征，但也带来了计算和工程方面的挑战。架构、正则化和训练过程的选择都取决于可用数据量。
